Reasoning: The paper proposes a framework to study models of computation of indeterministic data represented by abstract "distributions" using a fixed semi-ring. This topic is closely related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also characterizes decision problems solvable by polynomial uniform circuit families using invertible or "unitary" transformations over cyclic rings and finite fields, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses mathematical logic to study the power of different models of computation, which is related to the field of logic (cs.LO).
